subject: p19028690
Impression: Two frontal views of the chest show new mild interstitial pulmonary edema. Interval increase in mediastinal caliber therefore is probably due to distention of mediastinal veins. Heart size is slightly larger but still within normal range. Pleural effusions are minimal, if any. No focal pulmonary abnormality. No pneumothorax. ET tube is in standard placement and a nasogastric tube passes below the diaphragm and out of view.
